% query population and area database to find countries of approximately equal population density. 
query_pop([C1,D1,C2,D2]) :-
 
 
    density(C1, D1),
    density(C2, D2),
    C1 \= C2,
    20 * D1 < 21 * D2,
    20 * D2 < 21 * D1.
density(C,D) :-
 
 
    pop(C, P),
    area(C, A),
    D is (P * 100) // A.

The main differences are the addition of 'C1 \= C2' to avoid comparing the same country and the simplification of the density comparison conditions.
